pandas : manipulate data

> read_csv : 

> dataFrame objects : how pandas represents datasets
	> .describe() : summarizes the comuns and features
	> .shape
	> .values : returns values
	> .value_counts([normalize = True]) : counts the different values of the dataview
		> takes optional normalize argument that returns the value counts as proportions

	> filtering
		> data_frame["select_this_column"][data_frame["col"] == 'filter']
			> selects the first column but filters the data on another column

	> create new column
		> data_fram["new_var"] = 0

	> access multiple columns
		> data_frame[["col1", "col2"]]

	> group by
		> dataset.groupby('column_name').size()
			> shows row count for each different value in the specified column